gomodel:SYNGO_4511  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Amounts of anti-GluR2/3 antibody-immunoreactive AMPA receptor proteins were slightly increased in the mutant mice (p =0.005, Fig. 2A). The number of gold particles of AMPA receptors per profile of parallel fiber-Purkinje cell (PF-PC) synapses in the Delphilin mutant mice (6.460.3, n = 300 from 3 mice) was significantly larger than that in the wild-type mice (Fig. 2F).\nFig 3: Electrophysiological analysis of PF-PC synapses: Normal synaptic transmission in delphilin mutants as compared to WT. LTD was induced by 200 ms depolarization of a PC to -20 mV coupled with paired PF stimuli applied at 15 and 65 ms after the onset of depolarization. This conjunctive stimulation was repeated once, twice, 5X, 10X and 20X. Delphilin-deficient mutants displayed a much more efficient LTD after 2 and 5 conjunctions (Fig. 3A-E).\nEGTA experiments suggest that long-term depression (LTD) requires lower Ca2+ levels in Delphilin KO animals (Fig. 4B). Experimental description: LTD induction was facilitated at PF-PC synapses in Delphilin mutant mice (page 1, e2297). And: ...backcrossed 5 times to theC57BL/6 strain," ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4511" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

